.TH RESETUSB 8 "March 22, 2026" "resetusb" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
resetusb \- reset all enumerated USB devices on Linux
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B resetusb
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B resetusb
enumerates USB devices through
.BR libusb (3)
and issues a reset to every device it can open.
It is intended for controlled recovery operations when USB devices are stuck,
misbehaving, or need to be reprobed by the kernel.
.PP
This utility has no command-line options.
When invoked, it attempts to reset every enumerated USB device, including hubs.
That can interrupt keyboards, storage devices, serial adapters, and USB-backed
network interfaces.
.PP
Use
.B resetusb
only during controlled maintenance windows or other recovery procedures where
temporary USB disruption is acceptable.
.SH OUTPUT
For each successful reset,
.B resetusb
prints a line similar to:
.PP
.EX
reset bus 1 device 2 (1234:5678) Example Device
.EE
.PP
After successful initialization and device enumeration,
.B resetusb
prints a final summary line similar to:
.PP
.EX
Summary: reset 1 device(s), 0 failure(s)
.EE
.PP
Failures are written to standard error and include the bus number, device
address, vendor ID, product ID, product string when available, and the
underlying libusb error name.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
All attempted resets completed without failures.
.TP
.B 1
At least one reset failed, the process was not run with the required
privileges, the real and effective UIDs did not match, or libusb setup or
enumeration failed.
.SH REQUIREMENTS
.B resetusb
only runs on Linux and must be executed as root.
It refuses mismatched real and effective UID execution contexts.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/sbin/resetusb
Installed program path.
.TP
.I /usr/share/man/man8/resetusb.8
Installed manual page path.
.SH SAFETY
Because
.B resetusb
resets every enumerated USB device, it can disconnect the very peripherals
needed to manage the host.
Plan for console access or other recovery access before using it on remote
systems.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR libusb (3),
.BR lsusb (8)
.SH AUTHORS
resetusb maintainers
.SH HOMEPAGE
Project page:
.UR https://github.com/omkhar/resetusb
https://github.com/omkhar/resetusb
.UE
